title: Fans help Disneyland celebrate it's 60th birthday
text:
Updated: 1:39 p.m. Friday, July 17, 2015 | Posted: 1:03 p.m. Friday, July 17, 2015 Fans help Disneyland celebrate it's 60th birthday FILE - In this Sunday, July 17, 1955 file photo, children sprint across a drawbridge and into a castle that marks the entrance to Fantasyland at the opening of Walt Disney's Disneyland in Anaheim, Calif. Fantasyland had been closed until late in the day. (AP Photo) Related By Cox Media Group National Content Desk 
When it opened, Disneyland was like nothing that anyone had seen before.
